","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When initializing a new "},{"code":"InlineArray","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" value, you must initialize all of its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"elements. You can use an array literal just as with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Array"},{"type":"text","text":", rely on type"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"inference for the ","type":"text"},{"code":"count","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Element"},{"text":" type, and spell the type with the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"shorthand "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"[count of Element]"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"code":["let a: InlineArray<3, Int> = [1, 2, 3]","let b: InlineArray<_, Int> = [1, 2, 3]","let c: InlineArray<3, _>   = [1, 2, 3]","let d: InlineArray         = [1, 2, 3]","","let e: [3 of Int]          = [1, 2, 3]","let f: [_ of Int]          = [1, 2, 3]","let g: [3 of _]            = [1, 2, 3]","let h: [_ of _]            = [1, 2, 3]"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can also use one of the type’s initializers to create a new value."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"Accessing Elements","level":2,"anchor":"Accessing-Elements"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Just as with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Array"},{"type":"text","text":", you can read and modify an element in an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"InlineArray"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"using a subscript. Unless you use the memory-unsafe "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unchecked"},{"type":"text","text":" subscript,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"any index you provide is subject to bounds checking; an invalid index"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"triggers a runtime error in your program."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["var values: [3 of Double] = [1, 